00:41:18,824 --> 00:41:23,787
Cause of death: gunshot wound to the
head, not the trauma from the beating.

475
00:41:23,954 --> 00:41:28,125
- What else?
- Her and her friends were barhopping.

476
00:41:28,291 --> 00:41:31,336
We're interviewing anyone
who might have seen them.

477
00:41:31,503 --> 00:41:34,131
One other thing,
the backpack in her car...

478
00:41:34,297 --> 00:41:37,300
...had pamphlets on Las Vegas
and a list of Vegas hotels.

479
00:41:37,467 --> 00:41:39,761
It doesn't sound like much.

480
00:41:39,928 --> 00:41:42,139
What do you say, Devine?

481
00:41:43,849 --> 00:41:45,559
We'll get the guy, sir.

482
00:41:45,976 --> 00:41:49,855
That's right. All right, let's do it.

483
00:41:54,651 --> 00:41:58,655
- That's the best you can come up with?
- It made him happy, didn't it?

484
00:42:00,824 --> 00:42:02,784
This is Sean.

485
00:42:03,577 --> 00:42:06,955
- Hello?
- Is it Lauren?

486
00:42:09,708 --> 00:42:12,544
You're in Manhattan.
I can tell by the traffic sounds.

487
00:42:15,005 --> 00:42:16,715
Is he with you?

488
00:42:23,263 --> 00:42:25,432
Is that the baby?

489
00:42:26,850 --> 00:42:28,977
Lauren, at least tell me her name.

490
00:42:38,820 --> 00:42:41,490
Yeah, nice talking to you too.

491
00:42:55,420 --> 00:42:57,047
Hey.

492
00:43:00,509 --> 00:43:02,844
Would it surprise you?

493
00:43:03,011 --> 00:43:04,930
Wouldn't be the first time.

494
00:43:08,225 --> 00:43:11,061
Did you see that girl?
Did you see that...?

495
00:43:11,228 --> 00:43:13,230
Did you see her?

496
00:43:13,688 --> 00:43:16,733
- I heard a car hit something.
- Hit what? Another car?

497
00:43:16,900 --> 00:43:19,778
- Oh, no, not loud like that.
- Like hitting the curb?

498
00:43:19,945 --> 00:43:21,821
Yes, maybe.

499
00:43:21,988 --> 00:43:24,950
Then it stalled, and someone said, "Hi."

500
00:43:25,116 --> 00:43:27,244
- Someone said, "Hi"?
- "Hi."

501
00:43:28,703 --> 00:43:30,914
Then there was a loud crack.

502
00:43:31,081 --> 00:43:34,793
- Could it have been a gunshot?
- Yes, maybe.

503
00:43:34,960 --> 00:43:38,338
- Did you look out your window?
- Oh, no.

504
00:43:38,505 --> 00:43:41,466
I was in my dressing gown by then.

505
00:43:42,259 --> 00:43:45,095
I don't look out the window
in my dressing gown.

506
00:43:45,262 --> 00:43:47,931
The voice you heard,
was that a male or a female?

507
00:43:48,431 --> 00:43:50,558
Female.

508
00:43:50,725 --> 00:43:52,102
I think.

509
00:43:52,936 --> 00:43:56,022
- It sounds like the girl knew the shooter.
- Yeah.

510
00:43:56,189 --> 00:43:58,441
Sorry to trouble you.

511
00:44:06,449 --> 00:44:08,910
- Jimmy.
- Theo.

512
00:44:09,077 --> 00:44:11,413
How's my daughter?
How's Annabeth holding up?

513
00:44:11,579 --> 00:44:13,581
- She's trying.
- Let's get these on ice.

514
00:44:13,748 --> 00:44:16,126
You got a couple of coolers?

515
00:44:22,090 --> 00:44:24,300
Right here's fine.

516
00:44:29,472 --> 00:44:32,851
So how are you handling all this so far?

517
00:44:33,018 --> 00:44:35,979
- It hasn't really sunk in, Theo.
- Yeah?

518
00:44:36,146 --> 00:44:38,565
It's gonna hurt like hell when it does.

519
00:44:38,732 --> 00:44:42,485
When my Janey died,
I was no good for six months...

520
00:44:42,652 --> 00:44:46,448
...but my kids were
all grown up. I had that luxury.

521
00:44:46,614 --> 00:44:50,326
You, you got domestic responsibilities.

522
00:44:52,412 --> 00:44:54,330
Domestic responsibilities?

523
00:44:54,497 --> 00:44:59,794
Yeah, you gotta take care of my daughter
and those girls. That's your first priority.

524
00:45:00,378 --> 00:45:02,964
Oh, you figured that might
have slipped my mind?

525
00:45:03,131 --> 00:45:05,717
It just needed to be said, that's all.

526
00:45:06,843 --> 00:45:09,971
You'll come through
because you're a man.

527
00:45:10,138 --> 00:45:12,307
Like I said to Annabeth,
your wedding day.

528
00:45:12,474 --> 00:45:15,727
I said, "You got yourself
a real old-school man there."

529
00:45:15,894 --> 00:45:18,521
- Like they put her in a bag.
- What?

530
00:45:18,688 --> 00:45:21,900
That's what Katie looked like
when I saw her in the morgue.

531
00:45:22,066 --> 00:45:26,029
Like they put her in a bag
and then they beat the bag with pipes.

532
00:45:27,280 --> 00:45:29,866
- Well...
- Janey died in her sleep, all due respect.

533
00:45:30,033 --> 00:45:33,203
She went to sleep,
she never woke up. Peaceful.

534
00:45:33,536 --> 00:45:38,249
- You don't need to talk about Janey.
- My daughter was murdered.

535
00:45:38,416 --> 00:45:42,086
They put a gun to her. As we stand here,
she's on an autopsy slab...

536
00:45:42,253 --> 00:45:45,048
...getting cut open by scalpels
and chest spreaders...

537
00:45:45,215 --> 00:45:48,885
...and you're talking to me
about domestic fucking responsibility?

538
00:45:52,722 --> 00:45:54,933
Good to see you, Theo.

539
00:45:59,062 --> 00:46:02,565
Eve, just tell them what they
want to know.

540
00:46:02,732 --> 00:46:05,693
- Who was she dating?
- We already told the Savages.

541
00:46:05,860 --> 00:46:08,613
- The Savage brothers?
- They were here yesterday.

542
00:46:08,780 --> 00:46:12,158
Good, now try us out.
Who was she dating?

543
00:46:12,325 --> 00:46:14,619
No one special.

544
00:46:17,997 --> 00:46:21,251
You guys were having
a goodbye dinner, right?

545
00:46:22,001 --> 00:46:24,379
- What?
- She was leaving town, wasn't she?

546
00:46:24,546 --> 00:46:27,924
- Going to Las Vegas?
- How do you know?

547
00:46:28,091 --> 00:46:32,929
She closed her bank account,
she had hotel phone numbers.

548
00:46:33,930 --> 00:46:37,100
She wanted out of this dump.
She wanted to start a new life.

549
00:46:37,433 --> 00:46:40,770
Well, a 19-year-old girl
doesn't go to Las Vegas alone.

550
00:46:41,479 --> 00:46:43,815
So who was she going with?

551
00:46:43,982 --> 00:46:48,069
Come on, girls.
Who was she going with?

552
00:46:48,945 --> 00:46:50,238
Brendan.

553
00:46:50,571 --> 00:46:52,615
Excuse me?

554
00:46:52,782 --> 00:46:56,160
- Brendan.
- Brendan Harris?

555
00:46:56,619 --> 00:46:58,788
Brendan Harris, yeah.

556
00:46:58,997 --> 00:47:00,790
You got an address?

557
00:47:14,304 --> 00:47:16,264
Hey, Dave.

558
00:47:20,143 --> 00:47:22,061
Hey, Jimmy.

559
00:47:22,228 --> 00:47:25,690
Sorry, I came out for a smoke.

560
00:47:26,524 --> 00:47:29,402
Go ahead, sit down. Sit down.

561
00:47:34,991 --> 00:47:37,994
I haven't had a chance
to talk to you all day.

562
00:47:38,828 --> 00:47:40,830
How you doing?

563
00:47:41,330 --> 00:47:43,166
How you doing?

564
00:47:44,709 --> 00:47:46,586
What happened to your hand?

565
00:47:47,503 --> 00:47:49,088
This?

566
00:47:50,048 --> 00:47:54,343
I was helping a buddy move a couch.
I slammed it in the doorjamb.

567
00:47:55,511 --> 00:47:58,181
Ways you can manage
to hurt yourself, right?

568
00:48:00,516 --> 00:48:02,185
It's good to see you.

569
00:48:02,977 --> 00:48:04,312
Yeah?

570
00:48:10,359 --> 00:48:12,528
How are our girls holding up?

571
00:48:12,695 --> 00:48:14,822
They're doing okay, I guess.

572
00:48:14,989 --> 00:48:18,326
That Celeste, she's a godsend.
You thank her for me, will you?

573
00:48:30,087 --> 00:48:34,008
It's nice, isn't it? Just to sit out here.

574
00:48:36,302 --> 00:48:37,595
Yeah.

575
00:48:42,558 --> 00:48:46,562
I couldn't stand looking through the fridge
to find room for all that food...

576
00:48:46,729 --> 00:48:49,690
...we're gonna throw away
in the next few days.

577
00:48:49,982 --> 00:48:53,194
- Lot of waste, huh?
- Yeah.

578
00:48:54,570 --> 00:48:58,825
I just can't let anything get fucked up
in these next few days.

579
00:48:59,408 --> 00:49:03,913
Because it's all anybody
will remember about her.

580
00:49:10,169 --> 00:49:13,589
One thing you could say about Katie,
even when she was little...

581
00:49:14,799 --> 00:49:16,884
...that girl was neat.

582
00:49:20,221 --> 00:49:21,806
When I got out of the joint...

583
00:49:23,182 --> 00:49:26,102
...you know, after Marita died...

584
00:49:27,603 --> 00:49:32,608
...I remember, I was more afraid
of my little daughter...

585
00:49:33,776 --> 00:49:36,445
...than I ever was of being in prison.

586
00:49:44,912 --> 00:49:47,123
I loved her...

587
00:49:48,416 --> 00:49:50,334
...most...

588
00:49:53,004 --> 00:49:56,507
...because when we were sitting in that
kitchen that night...

589
00:49:59,385 --> 00:50:05,516
...it was like we were the last two people
on Earth. You know, forgotten.

590
00:50:06,183 --> 00:50:08,311
Unwanted.

591
00:50:10,396 --> 00:50:14,775
And it's really starting to piss me off,
Dave, because I can't cry for her.

592
00:50:14,942 --> 00:50:19,030
My own little daughter,
and I can't even cry for her.

593
00:50:23,993 --> 00:50:25,786
Jimmy.

594
00:50:29,915 --> 00:50:31,792
You're crying now.

595
00:50:35,004 --> 00:50:37,173
Yeah, damn.

596
00:50:42,219 --> 00:50:45,181
I just want to hug her one more time.

597
00:50:48,893 --> 00:50:52,605
She was 19 fucking years old.

598
00:50:59,904 --> 00:51:01,864
Do you want me to leave you alone?

599
00:51:02,865 --> 00:51:05,409
No, just stay here for a minute,
if that's cool.

600
00:51:06,577 --> 00:51:10,206
Yeah, sure. Jimmy, it's cool.

601
00:51:27,014 --> 00:51:29,850
When was the last time
you saw Katie Markum?

602
00:51:30,142 --> 00:51:33,604
- You don't think I'd hurt her do you?
- She isn't hurt. She's dead.

603
00:51:36,899 --> 00:51:40,569
- I didn't kill her.
- Again, when's the last time you saw her?

604
00:51:42,780 --> 00:51:46,075
About 8...
Saturday night, about 8:00.

605
00:51:46,367 --> 00:51:48,369
About like 8, Brendan, or at 8?

606
00:51:49,078 --> 00:51:50,913
It was about 8.

607
00:51:51,914 --> 00:51:56,919
We had a couple slices at Hi-Fi,
and she had to go meet Eve and Diane.

608
00:51:57,253 --> 00:52:00,589
Yeah. Why doesn't Jimmy Markum
like you?

609
00:52:02,132 --> 00:52:03,801
I don't know.

610
00:52:04,718 --> 00:52:09,431
But he told Katie he never wanted her
to see me or any other Harris.

611
00:52:09,598 --> 00:52:13,519
What? That thief thinks he's better
than our family?

612
00:52:13,686 --> 00:52:17,982
- He's not a thief.
- He's a thief! A scumbag burglar.

613
00:52:18,566 --> 00:52:22,319
Daughter probably had the same bad
gene. You count yourself lucky, Bren.

614
00:52:23,070 --> 00:52:27,616
So Katie had some brochures for Vegas.
We heard she was going there with you.

615
00:52:29,285 --> 00:52:31,787
We were gonna leave Sunday.

616
00:52:32,997 --> 00:52:35,916
We were gonna get married
when we got there.

617
00:52:38,127 --> 00:52:40,504
Well, that was the plan, right?

618
00:52:40,796 --> 00:52:43,674
You were gonna leave me?
Without a word?

619
00:52:43,841 --> 00:52:46,969
- Ma, I was gonna tell you.
- Just like your father, huh?

620
00:52:53,976 --> 00:52:58,147
That's my brother, Ray,
and his friend John.

621
00:52:58,314 --> 00:53:00,691
- Hey, boys.
- Hey.

622
00:53:00,941 --> 00:53:02,651
He don't speak.

623
00:53:02,818 --> 00:53:07,156
Father couldn't shut up, but his son's
a mute. Oh, yeah, life's fucking fair.

624
00:53:07,323 --> 00:53:11,452
They're here about Katie. Why don't you
go watch TV or something.

625
00:53:12,745 --> 00:53:16,957
So where were you between 12:30
and 2 A.M. on Sunday morning, Brendan?

626
00:53:17,791 --> 00:53:19,043
I was asleep.

627
00:53:19,209 --> 00:53:21,003
Can you confirm that, Mrs. Harris?

628
00:53:24,673 --> 00:53:27,968
I can confirm that he closed his door
at 10:00.

629
00:53:28,135 --> 00:53:30,929
He came down for breakfast at 9.

630
00:53:31,764 --> 00:53:36,393
I can't confirm that he didn't open
his window and go down the fire escape.

631
00:53:36,560 --> 00:53:40,731
Okay, we're gonna ask you to take a
polygraph. You think you'd be up for that?

632
00:53:43,400 --> 00:53:45,944
I loved her so much.

633
00:53:48,030 --> 00:53:50,741
I'm never gonna feel that again.

634
00:53:51,533 --> 00:53:53,702
It doesn't happen twice.

635
00:53:55,954 --> 00:53:58,165
Doesn't happen once most times.

636
00:53:59,708 --> 00:54:01,543
Celeste.

637
00:54:02,669 --> 00:54:06,715
- Sorry, Jimmy. You surprised me.
- What are you still doing here?

638
00:54:09,551 --> 00:54:11,178
I don't know.

639
00:54:11,970 --> 00:54:14,973
I don't know, I just...

640
00:54:16,141 --> 00:54:18,018
Did Annabeth get to sleep?

641
00:54:18,352 --> 00:54:20,896
Yeah, I convinced her to take a pill.

642
00:54:21,063 --> 00:54:24,066
- Could I get one of those?
- Yeah.

643
00:54:29,238 --> 00:54:31,698
One for the road and then home.

644
00:54:36,078 --> 00:54:40,749
Jimmy, I can stay over if you want.
Sit up with Annabeth.

645
00:54:40,916 --> 00:54:42,751
You've done enough.

646
00:54:47,131 --> 00:54:49,258
To you and Dave for being here for this.

647
00:55:06,441 --> 00:55:09,778
Okay, Jimmy. I'll be back.

648
00:55:11,113 --> 00:55:14,032
I'll be by first thing tomorrow.
See you first thing.

649
00:55:14,199 --> 00:55:15,868
Good night.

650
00:55:16,827 --> 00:55:19,454
- Good night.
- Yeah, good night.

651
00:55:39,141 --> 00:55:40,559
Hello?

652
00:55:44,313 --> 00:55:47,357
Christ. Lauren, say something.

653
00:55:53,530 --> 00:55:56,325
"Okay. Hey, Sean, how was your day?"

654
00:55:57,034 --> 00:56:00,787
<i>Oh, me? I'm tired of wishing things
made sense.</i>

655
00:56:00,954 --> 00:56:03,206
<i>I'm tired of caring about
some dead girl...</i>

656
00:56:03,373 --> 00:56:06,126
<i>...and there's just gonna be
another one after her.</i>

657
00:56:07,294 --> 00:56:11,757
Sending killers to jail is sending them
where they've been heading all their lives.

658
00:56:11,923 --> 00:56:13,967
The dead are still dead.

659
00:56:16,595 --> 00:56:18,930
Jesus, I...

660
00:56:19,097 --> 00:56:21,224
...can't do this tonight.

661
00:56:21,516 --> 00:56:23,310
I just...

662
00:56:24,353 --> 00:56:26,146
I can't do it.

663
00:56:26,521 --> 00:56:28,315
Bye, baby.

664
00:56:38,992 --> 00:56:40,619
Because...

665
00:56:41,745 --> 00:56:45,248
...sometimes the man wasn't a man at all.

666
00:56:45,457 --> 00:56:47,167
He was the boy.

667
00:56:48,085 --> 00:56:51,129
The boy who escaped from wolves.

668
00:56:52,214 --> 00:56:54,800
An animal of the dusk.

669
00:56:55,092 --> 00:56:56,968
Invisible.

670
00:56:57,386 --> 00:56:59,262
Silent.

671
00:56:59,846 --> 00:57:01,932
Living in a world...

672
00:57:02,099 --> 00:57:04,518
...the others never saw.

673
00:57:06,395 --> 00:57:08,897
World of fireflies.

674
00:57:10,482 --> 00:57:14,945
Unseen except as a flare
in the corner of your eye.

675
00:57:15,654 --> 00:57:20,075
Vanished by the time
you turn your head toward it.

676
00:57:31,628 --> 00:57:36,466
I just gotta get my head right.

677
00:57:39,427 --> 00:57:42,639
Catch a nice, long sleep.

678
00:57:43,098 --> 00:57:46,101
And the boy will go back to his forest.

679
00:57:48,186 --> 00:57:51,273
Back to his fireflies.

680
00:57:58,822 --> 00:58:00,282
Is he asleep?

681
00:58:21,887 --> 00:58:24,306
How's Jimmy and everybody?

682
00:58:25,390 --> 00:58:27,100
Okay.

683
00:58:27,392 --> 00:58:29,144
It's weird.

684
00:58:29,603 --> 00:58:33,523
Took something like this for me and him
to become friends again.

685
00:58:33,690 --> 00:58:36,151
Dave? Dave.

686
00:58:39,404 --> 00:58:41,364
There's still nothing in the paper.

687
00:58:41,990 --> 00:58:43,742
About what?

688
00:58:44,659 --> 00:58:45,952
About what?

689
00:58:48,663 --> 00:58:52,918
I don't know, honey. Maybe I didn't
hurt him as bad as I thought.

690
00:58:53,335 --> 00:58:55,962
He's a mugger. He's not going
to the hospital.

691
00:58:59,007 --> 00:59:00,675
Yeah.

692
00:59:00,842 --> 00:59:02,385
Right.

693
00:59:04,721 --> 00:59:07,307
Anyhow, it doesn't matter, does it?

694
00:59:08,099 --> 00:59:10,685
I mean, Katie Markum is dead.

695
00:59:11,853 --> 00:59:14,564
That seems more important right now.

696
00:59:43,718 --> 00:59:47,555
I know in my soul I contributed
to your death.

697
00:59:48,556 --> 00:59:51,059
But I don't know how.

698
01:00:10,912 --> 01:00:12,747
Brendan Harris aced his polygraph.

699
01:00:12,914 --> 01:00:15,583
Good. I didn't like him for it,
nor want him for it.

700
01:00:15,750 --> 01:00:17,085
Yeah. Poor fucking kid.

701
01:00:17,252 --> 01:00:21,256
Ballistics will be back in a while.
Meantime, we got a list of bar patrons.

702
01:00:21,423 --> 01:00:24,092
All people who, I'm certain,
are dying to cooperate.

703
01:00:24,259 --> 01:00:27,011
Considering the crime, maybe.

704
01:00:27,262 --> 01:00:28,596
Dave Boyle?

705
01:00:28,763 --> 01:00:32,225
Hey, is that the guy you were friends
with as a kid? The car guy?

706
01:00:32,684 --> 01:00:33,935
Could be.

707
01:00:34,102 --> 01:00:37,605
He's a guy to talk to. He knows you.
He won't treat us like cops.

708
01:00:37,772 --> 01:00:41,484
- Clam up for no reason, huh?
- We'll see.

709
01:00:52,745 --> 01:00:54,372
Hey, Boyle!

710
01:00:55,123 --> 01:00:57,500
- What's it been, seven, eight years?
- Yeah.

711
01:00:57,667 --> 01:00:59,169
Yeah. How you doing?

712
01:00:59,460 --> 01:01:00,795
This is my son, Michael.

713
01:01:00,962 --> 01:01:03,339
Hey, Michael. How you doing?
My name's Sean.

714
01:01:03,506 --> 01:01:06,384
I'm an old buddy of your dad's.
Hi.

715
01:01:07,051 --> 01:01:10,305
- So you still with the staties?
- Homicide. This is my partner.

716
01:01:10,471 --> 01:01:13,183
- Sergeant Powers. How are you?
- So you got a minute?

717
01:01:13,349 --> 01:01:17,645
- We'd love to ask some quick questions.
- I was just gonna walk Michael to school.

718
01:01:17,812 --> 01:01:21,733
- I can be back in a few minutes.
- Tell you what, we'll walk with you, okay?

719
01:01:21,900 --> 01:01:23,401
Sure.

720
01:01:24,986 --> 01:01:26,779
So you look good.

721
01:01:27,322 --> 01:01:30,325
- I hear rents are rising.
- Yeah, the yuppies are coming.

722
01:01:30,491 --> 01:01:33,119
They're cutting my dad's old house up
into condos.

723
01:01:33,286 --> 01:01:35,079
We walked by there the other day.

724
01:01:35,246 --> 01:01:37,498
Must be something we could do
to stop them.

725
01:01:37,665 --> 01:01:40,084
A friend of mine says the other day,
he says:

726
01:01:40,251 --> 01:01:44,714
"Neighborhood needs a crime wave.
Get property values where they belong."

727
01:01:44,881 --> 01:01:49,385
Girls keep getting murdered up in Pen
Park, Mr. Boyle, you might get your wish.

728
01:01:49,552 --> 01:01:52,055
Dave. Call me Dave.

729
01:01:52,221 --> 01:01:54,182
You said the F-word, Dad.

730
01:01:54,557 --> 01:01:57,352
Yeah, I know. Walk on up ahead, Michael.

731
01:01:57,518 --> 01:02:00,688
Us guys need to talk. Go on.

732
01:02:00,855 --> 01:02:04,859
- So, what's up, Sean?
- Yeah, you heard about Katie Markum?

733
01:02:05,026 --> 01:02:07,946
Yeah, I was at Jimmy's yesterday.
Celeste is there now.

734
01:02:08,112 --> 01:02:10,239
- Who's Celeste?
- My wife.

735
01:02:10,406 --> 01:02:14,661
- How's Jimmy doing?
- It's hard to tell. You know him.

736
01:02:14,827 --> 01:02:18,206
- Yeah, so the reason we came by...
- Listen, I saw her.

737
01:02:18,998 --> 01:02:23,419
Katie. I don't know if you know that.
At McGill's, the night she died.

738
01:02:23,586 --> 01:02:25,588
That's what we wanted to talk about.

739
01:02:25,755 --> 01:02:29,717
They were at a couple of bars that night.
Your name turned up for McGill's.

740
01:02:29,884 --> 01:02:32,178
They put on quite a show
dancing on the bar.

741
01:02:32,345 --> 01:02:35,890
- Pretty drunk, huh?
- But it was harmless.

742
01:02:36,057 --> 01:02:39,102
They weren't stripping or nothing.
They were just 19.

743
01:02:39,268 --> 01:02:40,853
What time did they leave?

744
01:02:41,020 --> 01:02:44,065
I left at 1. They must've left
15 minutes before me.

745
01:02:44,232 --> 01:02:47,360
- So we'll say 12:45?
- Sounds about right.

746
01:02:48,403 --> 01:02:51,030
You see anything unusual
or anyone...?

747
01:02:51,197 --> 01:02:52,865
Michael.

748
01:02:53,366 --> 01:02:55,076
Like what?
I don't know.

749
01:02:55,243 --> 01:02:56,577
A guy watching the girls?

750
01:02:56,744 --> 01:02:59,580
A guy with hate in his eyes?
A woman-hater?

751
01:03:00,915 --> 01:03:05,586
No. No, if they hadn't danced on the bar,
it would've been business as usual.

752
01:03:05,753 --> 01:03:09,090
- See you later, Dad.
- You got your milk money?

753
01:03:16,097 --> 01:03:18,099
Fuck, I hated school.

754
01:03:18,599 --> 01:03:20,143
What?

755
01:03:21,561 --> 01:03:24,647
Yeah, me too, Sean.

756
01:03:25,982 --> 01:03:30,319
Just one more thing, Mr. Boyle.
Where did you go after you left McGill's?

757
01:03:30,486 --> 01:03:33,614
- Home.
- Home by 1: 15, would you say?

758
01:03:33,781 --> 01:03:36,576
- Roughly. Sure.
- All right.

759
01:03:38,286 --> 01:03:41,330
Yeah, well, thanks a lot, Dave.
We'll grab a beer sometime?

760
01:03:41,789 --> 01:03:44,959
- Yeah, I'd like that, Sean.
- All right.

761
01:03:51,632 --> 01:03:53,217
What?

762
01:03:53,593 --> 01:03:55,970
What happened to him in that car?

763
01:04:03,311 --> 01:04:05,146
Can you believe this?

764
01:04:05,313 --> 01:04:09,317
Man, it's the same as Dunkin' Donuts.
It costs 15 times the price.

765
01:04:10,902 --> 01:04:14,363
You know, you take away love,
money or hate as motives...

766
01:04:14,530 --> 01:04:16,449
...you're not left with a whole lot.

767
01:04:16,616 --> 01:04:19,202
Well, if this Markum thing's random,
I mean, shit.

768
01:04:19,368 --> 01:04:23,581
Yeah, tell me about it. But the old lady,
Prior, she doesn't hear a scream.

769
01:04:23,748 --> 01:04:25,708
Hears a gunshot,
before that a "hi"...

770
01:04:25,875 --> 01:04:29,128
...which tells me the girl is either
friendly or she knew him.

771
01:04:29,295 --> 01:04:33,925
She turns to the curb, not too fast or she
hops it. Foot's off the clutch. She stalls.

772
01:04:34,091 --> 01:04:37,970
- She says, "Hi." He shoots her.
- She slams the door into him, takes off.

773
01:04:38,137 --> 01:04:40,806
What makes her swerve
without hitting the brakes?

774
01:04:40,973 --> 01:04:43,601
- I don't know. Something in the street.
- Maybe.

775
01:04:43,768 --> 01:04:47,021
This Markum girl couldn't have
weighed more than what, 110?

776
01:04:47,188 --> 01:04:51,484
- Hits hard enough to get a jump on him?
- Maybe he's knocked back on his heels.

777
01:04:51,651 --> 01:04:55,196
Your pal Dave strikes me as a guy
permanently back on his heels.

778
01:04:55,363 --> 01:04:58,574
Wait a second, how did we get to
Dave Boyle all of a sudden?

779
01:04:58,741 --> 01:05:01,452
- We just got to him.
- He's a guy who was in the bar.

780
01:05:01,619 --> 01:05:04,455
The last place, Seany,
the last place she was at.

781
01:05:04,622 --> 01:05:06,749
The guy is wrong. You saw his hand.

782
01:05:06,916 --> 01:05:10,586
Yeah, I saw his hand. You seriously
want to take a look at Dave Boyle?

783
01:05:10,753 --> 01:05:12,922
Just a little one.

784
01:05:17,927 --> 01:05:22,181
I'd recommend two sets of visiting hours,
from 3 to 5, and 7 to 9.

785
01:05:22,348 --> 01:05:24,517
- Sure.
- Good.

786
01:05:26,060 --> 01:05:30,856
- Have you thought about flowers?
- I'll call Knopfler's this afternoon.

787
01:05:31,190 --> 01:05:32,525
Good.

788
01:05:37,905 --> 01:05:39,824
And the notice?

789
01:05:40,658 --> 01:05:42,034
Notice?

790
01:05:43,411 --> 01:05:48,290
Yes, the obituary. We can take care of it
if you give us her basic information.

791
01:05:48,457 --> 01:05:51,043
Or if you prefer donations
in lieu of flowers?

792
01:05:51,210 --> 01:05:52,920
Where's my daughter?

793
01:05:55,423 --> 01:05:57,466
Downstairs, in the basement.

794
01:05:58,300 --> 01:05:59,593
I wanna see her.

795
01:06:46,974 --> 01:06:49,310
I'm gonna find him, Katie.

796
01:06:50,728 --> 01:06:53,814
I'm gonna find him before the police do.

797
01:06:54,190 --> 01:06:56,817
I'm gonna find the man,
and I'm gonna kill him.

798
01:07:00,738 --> 01:07:03,324
Did you say something, Mr. Markum?

799
01:07:06,785 --> 01:07:08,704
The notice.

800
01:07:09,997 --> 01:07:12,374
It should read: "Katherine Markum...

801
01:07:14,043 --> 01:07:17,546
...beloved daughter
of James and Marita, deceased...

802
01:07:18,297 --> 01:07:22,551
...stepdaughter of Annabeth, sister to..."

803
01:07:22,885 --> 01:07:26,347
"Sister to Sara and Nadine."

804
01:08:06,720 --> 01:08:10,766
- You guys again?
- Yeah. We're like two bad pennies.

805
01:08:11,725 --> 01:08:14,019
- You dropping in on Jimmy?
- Yeah.

806
01:08:14,186 --> 01:08:16,939
Do you have some kind of, what,
break in the case?

807
01:08:17,106 --> 01:08:20,109
No, just paying our respects.
Where you off to?

808
01:08:20,276 --> 01:08:24,905
Annabeth got a craving for cigarettes. I'm
gonna go get some. See you in a minute.

809
01:08:25,072 --> 01:08:28,909
By the way, Mr. Boyle, what happened
to your hand there?

810
01:08:30,577 --> 01:08:35,374
Garbage disposal. It jammed, I stuck
my hand in, it started again.

811
01:08:35,541 --> 01:08:37,251
- Stupid.
- Painful.

812
01:08:41,588 --> 01:08:43,924
Garbage disposal. Bullshit.

813
01:08:44,091 --> 01:08:48,095
Yeah. Well, it doesn't mean
he killed anybody either. Come on.

814
01:09:01,692 --> 01:09:04,737
- Heard you could use one.
- Thanks.

815
01:09:06,113 --> 01:09:10,451
- I quit 10 years ago, you believe this?
- Whatever you need right now.

816
01:09:12,161 --> 01:09:14,163
Come on in, I'll get Jimmy.

817
01:09:19,376 --> 01:09:22,504
I got a couple errands I gotta run.
I'll be back in an hour.

818
01:09:22,671 --> 01:09:25,340
You don't have to come back, Celeste.
I'll be fine.

819
01:09:25,507 --> 01:09:26,675
- Sure?
- Celeste Boyle?

820
01:09:26,842 --> 01:09:28,302
Yeah.

821
01:09:28,469 --> 01:09:31,889
I'm Sean Devine, an old friend of Dave's.
This is Whitey Powers.

822
01:09:32,055 --> 01:09:35,100
- Mrs. Boyle.
- Nice to meet you.

823
01:09:35,267 --> 01:09:36,769
Look, I gotta go.

824
01:09:39,646 --> 01:09:43,358
Oh, damn it.
I left my report pad in the cruiser.

825
01:09:43,525 --> 01:09:46,111
- You better go get it.
- Yeah.

826
01:09:46,945 --> 01:09:48,405
Come on.

827
01:09:53,494 --> 01:09:56,997
Hey, Celeste, could I ask you
a quick question?

828
01:09:57,539 --> 01:09:59,958
- Me?
- What time did Dave get home Saturday?

829
01:10:00,125 --> 01:10:01,752
- What?
- It's a little thing.

830
01:10:01,919 --> 01:10:05,672
We're running a time line on everything
involving Katie. I'm sure...

831
01:10:05,839 --> 01:10:07,883
...Dave told you he saw her
at McGill's.

832
01:10:09,468 --> 01:10:11,637
You think Dave killed Katie?

833
01:10:12,095 --> 01:10:15,349
Oh, no. God. I didn't say that.
Why would I even think that?

834
01:10:17,768 --> 01:10:21,188
- I don't know.
- No. It's just that we could figure out...

835
01:10:21,355 --> 01:10:24,942
...what time she was on the road
if we knew what time Dave got home.

836
01:10:25,108 --> 01:10:28,278
See, it's 5 minutes from your place
to McGill's...

837
01:10:28,445 --> 01:10:31,907
...and Katie left 15 minutes
before Dave did. You see what I mean.

838
01:10:32,366 --> 01:10:33,867
I was asleep.

839
01:10:36,537 --> 01:10:41,750
Saturday night, when Dave came in,
I was asleep.

840
01:10:41,917 --> 01:10:44,253
Okay. Well, thanks.

841
01:10:54,972 --> 01:10:56,723
Bullshit.

842
01:10:56,890 --> 01:10:58,392
No, he was dating Katie, Jim.

843
01:10:58,559 --> 01:11:02,229
They were gonna elope to Vegas.
We found tickets under their names.

844
01:11:02,396 --> 01:11:04,106
Brendan Harris confirmed it.

845
01:11:04,648 --> 01:11:05,899
Remember what you said?

846
01:11:06,400 --> 01:11:10,904
How she looked at you on Saturday like
she was preparing to never see you again?

847
01:11:12,531 --> 01:11:16,368
- Did Brendan Harris kill my daughter?
- No.

848
01:11:16,535 --> 01:11:18,120
You're 100 percent sure?

849
01:11:18,787 --> 01:11:23,083
Passed his poly with flying colors, plus it
seemed to me like he really loved her.

850
01:11:26,086 --> 01:11:29,006
Jimmy, I'm just curious, man.

851
01:11:29,172 --> 01:11:31,591
Why are you so dead set
against that kid?

852
01:11:31,758 --> 01:11:35,429
He said Katie told him you'd disown her
if she ever dated a Harris.

853
01:11:37,097 --> 01:11:40,267
I knew his father. They called him
"Just Ray" Harris.

854
01:11:40,434 --> 01:11:41,768
Why is that?

855
01:11:43,812 --> 01:11:46,440
There were so many Rays
in the neighborhood.

856
01:11:46,606 --> 01:11:50,777
You had "Crazy Ray" Bucheck,
"Psycho Ray" Dorian.

857
01:11:51,778 --> 01:11:54,948
The cool names were taken,
so he got stuck with "Just Ray."

858
01:11:55,115 --> 01:11:57,951
We never got along.
I flat out didn't like him.

859
01:11:58,785 --> 01:12:03,623
And he cut out on his wife when she was
pregnant with that little mute of hers.

860
01:12:04,041 --> 01:12:05,792
I don't know.

861
01:12:06,126 --> 01:12:08,962
I just figure the apple doesn't fall
far from the tree.

862
01:12:09,254 --> 01:12:14,301
I didn't want Brendan or any other Harris
dating Katie or any daughter of mine.

863
01:12:16,470 --> 01:12:19,264
I can't believe we're talking about
Just Ray Harris.

864
01:12:19,431 --> 01:12:21,975
How about this? We've interviewed
witnesses...

865
01:12:22,142 --> 01:12:24,311
...canvassed people
who were in the bar.

866
01:12:24,478 --> 01:12:28,482
We've run into more than a few of them
who were questioned...

867
01:12:28,648 --> 01:12:32,152
...before us by one or more
of the Savage brothers.

868
01:12:32,319 --> 01:12:35,614
- So?
- So the Savages are not policemen, Jim.

869
01:12:35,781 --> 01:12:39,534
- Some people don't talk to policemen.
- With all due respect...

870
01:12:39,701 --> 01:12:42,204
...and just so we're clear,
this is our case.

871
01:12:42,954 --> 01:12:45,373
- How long?
- How long what?

872
01:12:45,707 --> 01:12:48,168
How long before you catch
my daughter's killer?

873
01:12:48,335 --> 01:12:49,669
You bargaining with us?

874
01:12:51,505 --> 01:12:52,798
Bargaining?

875
01:12:54,508 --> 01:12:56,343
You giving us a deadline?

876
01:12:59,346 --> 01:13:03,183
We'll speak for Katie, Mr. Markum.
If that's okay with you.

877
01:13:04,434 --> 01:13:08,939
Just find my daughter's killer, sergeant.
I'm not standing in your way.

878
01:13:12,734 --> 01:13:16,696
The last thing we need is Markum
and the Savages putting the fear of God...

879
01:13:16,863 --> 01:13:19,908
...into the neighborhood.
- We grew up terrified of those brothers.

880
01:13:20,075 --> 01:13:23,703
Eleven months apart, like their mother ran
a loose-cannon factory.

881
01:13:23,870 --> 01:13:26,331
Fucking knuckleheads.

882
01:13:29,376 --> 01:13:31,461
Ballistics are in on the Markum murder.

883
01:13:31,628 --> 01:13:35,006
- Yeah, you got a match?
- You're gonna love it.

884
01:13:36,174 --> 01:13:39,553
It's a perfect match.
Gun was a.38 Smith.

885
01:13:39,719 --> 01:13:44,015
Part of a lot stolen from a gun dealer
in New Hampshire in 1982.

886
01:13:44,182 --> 01:13:49,312
The gun that killed Katherine Markum
was used in a liquor-store holdup in 1984.

887
01:13:49,479 --> 01:13:50,855
- In Buckingham.
- The Flats?

888
01:13:51,022 --> 01:13:55,652
Rome Basin. Place called Looney Liquors.
I pulled the file.

889
01:13:55,819 --> 01:13:59,906
It was a two-man job.
They fired a warning shot into a wall.

890
01:14:00,073 --> 01:14:03,702
- That's where the bullet got pulled.
- Nice work.

891
01:14:03,868 --> 01:14:06,037
Thought you'd like that.

892
01:14:35,734 --> 01:14:37,652
It's okay, Ray.

893
01:14:38,445 --> 01:14:40,280
Don't worry about it.

894
01:14:54,294 --> 01:14:55,628
Ma said that?

895
01:14:58,214 --> 01:14:59,466
That I'm better off?

896
01:15:05,347 --> 01:15:08,308
I loved her!
You know what that's like?

897
01:15:08,725 --> 01:15:09,976
Huh?

898
01:15:15,148 --> 01:15:16,983
I'm sorry.

899
01:15:25,075 --> 01:15:26,910
No, you're wrong.

900
01:15:28,078 --> 01:15:30,330
I won't ever feel that again.

901
01:15:31,122 --> 01:15:36,294
Right there. Went in through a bottle
of Jack and stuck in the wall right there.

902
01:15:36,461 --> 01:15:40,340
- Scary, huh?
- Scarier than a glass of milk, right?

903
01:15:40,507 --> 01:15:43,051
So take me through it.
These two guys come in...

904
01:15:43,259 --> 01:15:47,097
In rubber masks.
They came in through here.

905
01:15:49,432 --> 01:15:51,976
That's the storeroom.

906
01:15:52,977 --> 01:15:56,689
There's a door back there
that leads to a loading dock.

907
01:15:56,981 --> 01:15:59,192
I always keep that door locked.

908
01:15:59,901 --> 01:16:02,862
So they must have had a key.

909
01:16:03,029 --> 01:16:07,033
A key? So, what you're saying
is that it was an inside job?

910
01:16:07,200 --> 01:16:11,496
It had to be. One of them, at least,
worked for me at some point.

911
01:16:11,663 --> 01:16:16,376
The only reason they fired that warning
shot was they must have known...

912
01:16:16,793 --> 01:16:18,545
...I kept this under the counter.

913
01:16:18,711 --> 01:16:22,340
- And you told the police that at the time.
- Yeah.

914
01:16:23,258 --> 01:16:25,802
Sure, they went through
my employment records.

915
01:16:25,969 --> 01:16:28,555
Questioned everybody
who used to work for me.

916
01:16:28,721 --> 01:16:31,808
- Never made an arrest.
- Still have a copy of those records?

917
01:16:31,975 --> 01:16:36,896
Yeah, it's in a box in the office there.
But I know who did it.

918
01:16:37,063 --> 01:16:38,565
Oh, yeah?

919
01:16:38,731 --> 01:16:41,442
This guy I fired a couple
of weeks before.

920
01:16:41,609 --> 01:16:45,530
Son of a bitch came in here
a few days after the robbery.

921
01:16:45,697 --> 01:16:49,909
He had this fucking goddamn grin
on his face.

922
01:16:50,076 --> 01:16:52,161
And I just knew.

923
01:16:52,328 --> 01:16:55,081
Go tell a grin to a jury, right?

924
01:16:55,748 --> 01:16:57,584
You remember his name?

925
01:16:58,585 --> 01:17:00,545
Do I look senile to you?

926
01:17:00,920 --> 01:17:03,214
- No, sir.
- Name...

927
01:17:03,423 --> 01:17:05,425
...was Ray Harris.

928
01:17:05,800 --> 01:17:08,845
We used to call him "Just Ray."

929
01:17:11,598 --> 01:17:14,642
You say they used the same gun
for another crime?

930
01:17:15,643 --> 01:17:19,355
- That's correct, sir.
- Thanks for your help, Mr. Looney.

931
01:17:31,284 --> 01:17:33,161
Where you been?

932
01:17:34,454 --> 01:17:36,164
Out.

933
01:17:39,417 --> 01:17:41,419
What you watching?

934
01:17:41,586 --> 01:17:43,671
Some vampire movie.

935
01:17:44,380 --> 01:17:46,966
Guy just got his head torn off.

936
01:17:48,718 --> 01:17:50,887
Where'd you go, Celeste?

937
01:17:55,224 --> 01:17:57,477
I was sitting in my car...

938
01:17:57,935 --> 01:18:01,105
...down by the channel.
You know...

939
01:18:01,731 --> 01:18:03,149
...thinking about things.

940
01:18:04,984 --> 01:18:08,363
- What'd you think about?
- Oh, you know...

941
01:18:08,780 --> 01:18:11,783
No, actually, I don't know.

942
01:18:17,497 --> 01:18:20,833
Things. You know, the day.

943
01:18:22,460 --> 01:18:25,296
About Katie being dead.

944
01:18:25,880 --> 01:18:28,716
And poor Annabeth and Jimmy,
you know...

945
01:18:29,425 --> 01:18:31,302
...those things.

946
01:18:31,677 --> 01:18:33,679
Those things.

947
01:18:34,472 --> 01:18:36,891
Know what I was thinking about, huh?

948
01:18:38,518 --> 01:18:40,061
Vampires.

949
01:18:41,771 --> 01:18:43,022
What about them?

950
01:18:44,899 --> 01:18:48,027
