themselves, but...

981
01:20:57,823 --> 01:21:01,369
...they were wolves, and Dave...

982
01:21:02,036 --> 01:21:06,082
...was the boy who escaped from wolves.

983
01:21:08,292 --> 01:21:10,461
What are you talking about, Dave?

984
01:21:11,003 --> 01:21:13,381
I'm talking Henry and George.

985
01:21:14,382 --> 01:21:17,176
They took me on a four-day ride.

986
01:21:17,885 --> 01:21:23,224
They buried me in this ratty old cellar
with a sleeping bag.

987
01:21:24,058 --> 01:21:26,977
And, man, Celeste...

988
01:21:27,186 --> 01:21:28,896
...did they have their fun.

989
01:21:30,856 --> 01:21:34,235
And no one came to help old Dave then.

990
01:21:36,237 --> 01:21:41,033
Dave had to pretend to be somebody else.

991
01:21:46,038 --> 01:21:48,666
You mean, all those years ago...

992
01:21:51,544 --> 01:21:53,963
...when you were a little boy?

993
01:21:55,631 --> 01:21:57,258
Dave...

994
01:21:57,424 --> 01:21:59,510
Dave's dead.

995
01:22:00,886 --> 01:22:05,015
I don't know who came out of that cellar,
but it sure as shit wasn't Dave!

996
01:22:06,392 --> 01:22:07,810
You see, honey...

997
01:22:07,977 --> 01:22:09,478
Fuck!

998
01:22:09,728 --> 01:22:12,356
It's like vampires.

999
01:22:15,401 --> 01:22:17,403
Once it's in you...

1000
01:22:18,821 --> 01:22:20,739
...it stays.

1001
01:22:22,116 --> 01:22:24,160
What stays?

1002
01:22:30,833 --> 01:22:34,044
Did you know there were child prostitutes
in Rome Basin?

1003
01:22:34,920 --> 01:22:36,380
What?

1004
01:22:42,178 --> 01:22:43,679
Fuck!

1005
01:22:46,932 --> 01:22:49,935
I can't trust my mind anymore, Celeste.

1006
01:22:50,102 --> 01:22:52,104
I'm warning you...

1007
01:22:53,939 --> 01:22:55,774
...I can't trust my mind.

1008
01:22:58,736 --> 01:23:02,698
I gotta go out,
try to get my head around it.

1009
01:23:04,491 --> 01:23:05,993
Okay.

1010
01:23:10,539 --> 01:23:12,041
Okay.

1011
01:23:12,499 --> 01:23:13,918
Okay.

1012
01:23:15,628 --> 01:23:19,506
- The gun sends us in a different direction.
- I don't see it that way.

1013
01:23:19,673 --> 01:23:22,259
What does Just Ray's gun
have to do with Dave?

1014
01:23:22,426 --> 01:23:24,219
These things get passed around.

1015
01:23:24,386 --> 01:23:27,348
Just Ray may have blown town,
but his gun never did.

1016
01:23:27,514 --> 01:23:30,434
I say we talk with Brendan Harris
in the morning.

1017
01:23:30,601 --> 01:23:34,688
And I say Dave Boyle. The hand story.
The wife, she's definitely scared.

1018
01:23:34,855 --> 01:23:39,318
They're hiding something, but Boyle's
as much a killer as Brendan Harris.

1019
01:23:39,485 --> 01:23:43,656
Boyle fits the profile, a fucking T.
Mid-30s, white, marginally employed...

1020
01:23:43,822 --> 01:23:47,993
...sexually abused as a kid. On paper,
this guy should be in jail already.

1021
01:23:48,160 --> 01:23:50,496
Katie Markum
was not sexually abused, see?

1022
01:23:50,663 --> 01:23:54,041
In that equation,
sexual emission is part of the deal.

1023
01:23:54,208 --> 01:23:58,212
You were friends when you were kids.
This makes you a fucking liability.

1024
01:23:58,379 --> 01:23:59,672
He's not my friend.

1025
01:23:59,838 --> 01:24:04,343
Turns out you're right, I'll have my cuffs
off my hip faster than yours.

1026
01:24:18,941 --> 01:24:20,567
Hey, Jimmy.

1027
01:24:21,819 --> 01:24:23,362
You're out late.

1028
01:24:23,529 --> 01:24:25,239
Yeah, you too.

1029
01:24:26,699 --> 01:24:28,492
It's cold, huh?

1030
01:24:28,742 --> 01:24:30,994
Yeah, I guess.

1031
01:24:38,460 --> 01:24:40,045
You know, I...

1032
01:24:40,546 --> 01:24:42,589
I been sitting out here...

1033
01:24:42,756 --> 01:24:44,883
...over the last few years...

1034
01:24:46,802 --> 01:24:50,889
...waiting on Katie to get back
from someplace.

1035
01:24:51,890 --> 01:24:56,895
About midnight, I'd say to Annabeth,
"I'm gonna sit on the porch for a while."

1036
01:25:01,442 --> 01:25:03,277
Weird thing is...

1037
01:25:04,153 --> 01:25:06,238
...it seemed to bring her back.

1038
01:25:10,742 --> 01:25:12,786
I saw her, you know.

1039
01:25:14,621 --> 01:25:16,290
Saw who?

1040
01:25:16,540 --> 01:25:19,626
Katie. I was at McGill's Saturday night.

1041
01:25:21,628 --> 01:25:25,757
- You saw Katie Saturday night?
- Never got around to telling you.

1042
01:25:28,760 --> 01:25:30,429
Did you talk to her?

1043
01:25:31,263 --> 01:25:33,765
Just nodded hello at one point.

1044
01:25:34,600 --> 01:25:37,102
Next time I looked up, she was gone.

1045
01:25:43,317 --> 01:25:44,818
But...

1046
01:25:44,985 --> 01:25:46,570
...Jimmy...

1047
01:25:48,030 --> 01:25:49,948
...she looked...

1048
01:25:51,283 --> 01:25:52,784
...happy.

1049
01:26:09,801 --> 01:26:12,971
I got more walking to do.
Good night.

1050
01:26:24,858 --> 01:26:28,111
- You stole his car.
- His car was officially towed.

1051
01:26:28,278 --> 01:26:32,115
- From the front of his house.
- No! It was abandoned in Rome Basin...

1052
01:26:32,282 --> 01:26:33,784
...adjacent to the parkway.

1053
01:26:33,951 --> 01:26:38,497
Lucky for us, the parkway's state
jurisdiction. Some kids jacked the car...

1054
01:26:38,664 --> 01:26:42,250
...they took it for a joy ride...
- What? Why'd you do it?

1055
01:26:42,417 --> 01:26:47,339
After I left you last night, I decided to talk
to Boyle myself, put some fear into him.

1056
01:26:47,506 --> 01:26:52,302
I get to his house, I decide to look in
his car, see what he's got. I find blood.

1057
01:26:52,469 --> 01:26:55,180
- Blood?
- Front seat of Dave's car. B-negative.

1058
01:26:55,347 --> 01:26:59,184
- How much?
- A bit. Found more in the trunk. A lot.

1059
01:26:59,351 --> 01:27:02,187
Type O, same type as Katie Markum.

1060
01:27:02,354 --> 01:27:05,107
Wait, Katie Markum
never got in anybody's trunk.

1061
01:27:05,273 --> 01:27:08,026
She was chased through the park
where she died.

1062
01:27:08,193 --> 01:27:12,030
- It's enough to ask questions.
- Your search is gonna get tossed out.

1063
01:27:12,197 --> 01:27:17,077
No, found and abandoned in state
jurisdiction, for insurance purposes.

1064
01:27:17,244 --> 01:27:21,373
- In the best interest of the owner.
- Get a physical search, file the report.

1065
01:27:21,540 --> 01:27:23,041
Bingo.

1066
01:27:23,709 --> 01:27:26,378
You wanna talk to him,
or should I send him home?

1067
01:27:26,712 --> 01:27:29,715
- Dave's here?
- I've had him in the box for an hour.

1068
01:27:29,881 --> 01:27:33,009
Sent two of my biggest, ugliest troopers
to pick him up.

1069
01:27:34,803 --> 01:27:36,054
Come on, Mr. Boyle!

1070
01:27:36,221 --> 01:27:39,433
We know you didn't get that swollen hand
sticking it in the garbage disposal.

1071
01:27:40,058 --> 01:27:44,855
- Oh, yeah? How do you know that?
- Why's your wife afraid of you?

1072
01:27:45,397 --> 01:27:47,899
She know what really happened
to your hand?

1073
01:27:54,197 --> 01:27:57,075
How about a Sprite or something?

1074
01:27:57,242 --> 01:28:01,288
How about you tell us what really
happened Saturday night, Mr. Boyle?

1075
01:28:01,455 --> 01:28:02,998
You lied.

1076
01:28:03,165 --> 01:28:05,709
That's your opinion,
which you're entitled to.

1077
01:28:05,876 --> 01:28:10,755
- Hey, you think this is funny?
- No, I don't. I'm tired, I'm hung-over.

1078
01:28:10,922 --> 01:28:15,385
Not only was my car stolen last night,
but now you won't release it to me.

1079
01:28:15,552 --> 01:28:17,137
Okay.

1080
01:28:18,638 --> 01:28:20,307
All right.

1081
01:28:20,765 --> 01:28:23,935
Tell us, Mr. Boyle,
how did you get the blood in your car?

1082
01:28:24,102 --> 01:28:26,771
- What blood?
- Let's start with the front seat.

1083
01:28:28,690 --> 01:28:30,692
What are you looking at him for?

1084
01:28:32,152 --> 01:28:35,822
Hey, you think I could get
that Sprite, Sean?

1085
01:28:36,615 --> 01:28:38,116
Sure.

1086
01:28:38,408 --> 01:28:40,410
Oh, I get it.

1087
01:28:41,036 --> 01:28:42,871
You're the good cop.

1088
01:28:43,371 --> 01:28:46,416
How about a meatball sub
while you're at it?

1089
01:28:46,625 --> 01:28:49,794
I ain't your bitch, Dave.
Looks like you'll have to wait.

1090
01:28:50,921 --> 01:28:54,174
Yeah, but you're someone's bitch,
aren't you, Sean?

1091
01:28:56,343 --> 01:28:59,846
The blood on your front seat, Dave.
Answer the sergeant.

1092
01:29:02,599 --> 01:29:05,727
We got a chainlink fence
in our back yard.

1093
01:29:05,894 --> 01:29:09,105
Me and my kid play Wiffle Ball
every afternoon after school.

1094
01:29:09,731 --> 01:29:13,902
He's getting good, so most of the balls
are on the other side of the fence.

1095
01:29:14,069 --> 01:29:16,738
So I climb it.
Except I slip...

1096
01:29:16,905 --> 01:29:20,116
...slice myself where the links curl in,
right here.

1097
01:29:20,283 --> 01:29:22,077
Bled like hell.

1098
01:29:22,494 --> 01:29:25,747
Ten minutes later,
I gotta pick up Michael at school.

1099
01:29:26,331 --> 01:29:29,501
Probably was still bleeding
when I got in the front seat.

1100
01:29:29,668 --> 01:29:31,378
What blood type are you?

1101
01:29:32,045 --> 01:29:33,713
B-negative.

1102
01:29:33,964 --> 01:29:36,675
Yeah? That's the match we got.

1103
01:29:37,258 --> 01:29:39,344
- Well, there you go.
- Not quite.

1104
01:29:39,511 --> 01:29:42,013
Blood in the trunk of the car
wasn't B-negative.

1105
01:29:43,348 --> 01:29:46,184
I don't know anything
about any blood in the trunk.

1106
01:29:46,851 --> 01:29:50,021
No idea how half a pint of blood
got in the trunk?

1107
01:29:50,188 --> 01:29:53,358
- None.
- This is not the way you wanna go, Dave.

1108
01:29:53,525 --> 01:29:55,235
How will that look in court?

1109
01:29:55,402 --> 01:29:59,322
You not knowing how someone else's
blood got in the trunk of your car?

1110
01:29:59,489 --> 01:30:02,409
Gonna look fine, I suppose.
You filed the report.

1111
01:30:02,909 --> 01:30:04,703
What report?

1112
01:30:05,078 --> 01:30:09,374
The stolen-car report. The car
wasn't in my possession last night.

1113
01:30:09,708 --> 01:30:12,794
So whatever the thieves used it for,
you should find out...

1114
01:30:12,961 --> 01:30:15,547
...because it sounds like they
were up to no good.

1115
01:30:21,553 --> 01:30:25,056
Things looking any better
on the Sprite, Sean?

1116
01:30:25,306 --> 01:30:28,852
Well, you just got too fucking smart.
The car is inadmissible.

1117
01:30:29,018 --> 01:30:31,688
Anything there, his lawyers say
was put by thieves.

1118
01:30:31,855 --> 01:30:34,441
- I can break him.
- He just kicked our asses!

1119
01:30:34,607 --> 01:30:36,776
You still think Dave
wouldn't hurt a fly...

1120
01:30:36,943 --> 01:30:39,237
- Is that the point? No.
- What is the point?

1121
01:30:39,404 --> 01:30:43,408
We can break this open on the gun.
It's the gun.

1122
01:30:43,742 --> 01:30:46,077
Okay. Maybe.

1123
01:30:48,580 --> 01:30:50,248
So, what do we do with Dave?

1124
01:30:51,916 --> 01:30:53,460
Fuck it. Kick him loose.

1125
01:30:54,335 --> 01:30:58,256
Maybe a Celtic cross.
That's always a popular choice.

1126
01:30:58,465 --> 01:31:01,760
Or this lovely red marble here.

1127
01:31:02,594 --> 01:31:04,429
Or a figural.

1128
01:31:04,596 --> 01:31:06,181
That one.

1129
01:31:06,681 --> 01:31:10,185
Very good. Nice and simple.

1130
01:31:18,651 --> 01:31:20,278
Hey, Jimmy!

1131
01:31:23,698 --> 01:31:25,867
Annabeth said you were here.

1132
01:31:27,202 --> 01:31:29,329
We been asking around, like you said to.

1133
01:31:29,496 --> 01:31:31,039
- Yeah?
- Yeah.

1134
01:31:31,206 --> 01:31:34,417
Jimmy, this ain't about the two-year bit
you did for me.

1135
01:31:34,584 --> 01:31:37,670
And it ain't about me missing your brains
running things.

1136
01:31:37,837 --> 01:31:42,258
Katie was my niece. Not by birth, but
she was part of our family, we loved her.

1137
01:31:42,425 --> 01:31:44,969
I don't question you, Val.
What's up?

1138
01:31:46,346 --> 01:31:51,142
Cops are all over this. Doing their job
for once. Bars, street trade, everything.

1139
01:31:51,309 --> 01:31:54,771
Every hooker we talked to, bartender,
already been questioned.

1140
01:31:54,938 --> 01:31:58,816
- The fucking law has descended, Jimmy.
- What about Just Ray's kid?

1141
01:31:58,983 --> 01:32:02,862
Quiet as a mouse.
Kid's no trouble to anyone.

1142
01:32:03,112 --> 01:32:06,324
I talked to Diane and Eve.
They said he loved her.

1143
01:32:06,616 --> 01:32:09,160
Jimmy, they said that she loved him.

1144
01:32:11,162 --> 01:32:13,665
- Want us to take a run at him?
- No.

1145
01:32:13,831 --> 01:32:17,502
Hold off for now.
Anything else?

1146
01:32:20,296 --> 01:32:21,798
What?

1147
01:32:24,926 --> 01:32:27,637
Val, you wanna spit something, spit it.

1148
01:32:27,804 --> 01:32:29,347
Tell him.

1149
01:32:31,015 --> 01:32:34,018
Sean Devine and his partner
went by and saw Dave Boyle.

1150
01:32:34,185 --> 01:32:37,897
Dave was at McGill's. Probably
questioning him like everybody else.

1151
01:32:38,606 --> 01:32:40,900
I heard something else
this morning too.

1152
01:32:41,067 --> 01:32:45,738
- Two staties came by in uniform.
- Maybe they forgot to ask him something.

1153
01:32:46,364 --> 01:32:49,117
No. When they left,
they took him with them.

1154
01:32:49,284 --> 01:32:52,370
They put him in the back seat,
if you know what I mean.

1155
01:33:07,885 --> 01:33:11,639
"Raymond Matthew Harris,
born 9-6, 1957.

1156
01:33:11,806 --> 01:33:14,434
First child, Brendan Seamus,
born 1983."

1157
01:33:14,600 --> 01:33:19,230
Same year that Just Ray is indicted
in a scam to embezzle subway tokens.

1158
01:33:19,397 --> 01:33:21,733
Charges are dropped, and he's fired.

1159
01:33:21,899 --> 01:33:26,070
Does odd jobs after that,
including clerking at Looney Liquors.

1160
01:33:26,237 --> 01:33:31,159
Questioned in that robbery. Questioned in
another, same year, Blanchard Liquors...

1161
01:33:31,325 --> 01:33:33,578
...released on lack of evidence again.

1162
01:33:33,745 --> 01:33:37,123
- Beginning to become known, though.
- He's getting popular.

1163
01:33:37,290 --> 01:33:40,835
"A known associate, one Edmund Reese,
fingers Raymond...

1164
01:33:41,002 --> 01:33:44,589
...in the 1985 heist
of a rare comic-book collection."

1165
01:33:44,756 --> 01:33:46,257
Comic books? You go, Ray.

1166
01:33:46,424 --> 01:33:49,093
Hey, excuse me,
$150,000 worth of comic books.

1167
01:33:49,260 --> 01:33:51,012
Oh, excuse me.

1168
01:33:51,179 --> 01:33:56,100
"Raymond returned said literature
unharmed." Does a year solid inside.

1169
01:33:56,768 --> 01:33:59,270
Comes out with a chemical-dependency
problem.

1170
01:33:59,437 --> 01:34:01,939
Gets honest work
to support the habit, though?

1171
01:34:02,106 --> 01:34:03,983
Evidently not.

1172
01:34:04,150 --> 01:34:08,488
Picked up in a joint
MCU-FBI sting operation...

1173
01:34:08,654 --> 01:34:13,117
...trafficking stolen goods across
state lines. Stole a truckload of cigarettes.

1174
01:34:13,284 --> 01:34:16,120
- The boy's got style.
- Got a boatload of grief too.

1175
01:34:16,287 --> 01:34:20,958
Stole the truck in Rhode Island,
drove it into Massachusetts.

1176
01:34:21,125 --> 01:34:25,963
- Hence, the federal interstate rap.
- Hence, they got him by the balls, but...

1177
01:34:26,130 --> 01:34:27,799
...he does no time.

1178
01:34:28,591 --> 01:34:32,011
- He rolled on someone.
- Looks that way. After that, he's clean.

1179
01:34:32,178 --> 01:34:36,474
- August 1989, he disappears.
- One, dead, two, in Witness Protection.

1180
01:34:36,641 --> 01:34:39,936
Three, he goes deep underground,
then pops back up...

1181
01:34:40,102 --> 01:34:43,689
...to murder his son's 19-year-old
girlfriend? We got nothing.

1182
01:34:43,856 --> 01:34:48,486
A prime suspect in a robbery 18 years
ago, during which the weapon was used.

1183
